message: Focus on creating liquid items. The 'vial' tool is key: use it on solid ingredients to create 'extracted' liquids. Avoid using the vial on gas ingredients, as it results in negative value. The best combination for 100 value is combining a 'magical extracted liquid' with a 'mundane extracted liquid'. If you get a 70-value liquid blend (e.g., a raw magical liquid combined with an extracted mundane liquid), applying the 'filter' tool to it will increase its value to 80. Avoid filtering single extracted liquids or blends made from two magical extracted liquids, as this will reduce their value significantly. Note: The 'vial' tool appears to be reusable, despite the game's general rule about tools.

message: The most effective strategy I found for high scores is to combine one magical liquid and one mundane liquid ingredient, then apply the 'filter' tool to the resulting item; this consistently yielded 100 points. Alternatively, combining two mundane liquid ingredients and then using the 'filter' can give 60 points. Also, combining two magical gas ingredients and then using the 'filter' can lead to 60 points even from negative starting values. The 'vial' tool tended to decrease item values, and combinations involving solid ingredients were generally low or negative in value.

message: Hello! I found great success by using the 'vial' tool on solid ingredients. Using the vial on a magical solid (like dragon scale or unicorn horn) or a mundane solid (like obsidian or sunstone) consistently produced valuable liquid extracts. The ultimate high-score combination was a MAGICAL liquid extract (e.g., dragon scale extract) combined with a MUNDANE liquid extract (e.g., obsidian liquid extract), which yielded 100. The 'filter' tool can sometimes improve combined liquids, or even salvage negatively valued items, so don't be afraid to experiment with it on mixtures. Avoid using the vial on gases, as it typically creates negative-value, 'botched extraction' items. Good luck!

Avoid using the vial on gas items or combining liquids with gases, as these generally result in negative values.

message: Focus on creating a liquid mundane item and a liquid magical item. The best path for a liquid mundane is often using the 'vial' on a solid, mundane ingredient (e.g., rose petal + vial -> rose petal extract). For a liquid magical item, sometimes using 'filter' on a gas, magical ingredient works well (e.g., dragon's breath + filter -> filtered dragon's breath). Once you have one liquid mundane and one liquid magical item, combine them. If the resulting item isn't 100, try using the 'filter' tool on it. Avoid combining two gas items or using the vial on gas items, as these often lead to negative values.
